# Testing Rules (Flutter/Dart)

Testing is a **hard quality gate**, not an optional validation step.

All tests must be:
- deterministic
- isolated
- repeatable
- architecture-aware
- CI-safe

---

# 1. Required Test Coverage

## Mandatory Coverage Areas

- [ ] domain layer → unit tests required
- [ ] data layer → unit tests required (mock external dependencies)
- [ ] presentation layer → widget tests required
- [ ] critical flows → integration tests required

---

## Minimum Requirement

- all business logic must be tested
- all user-facing flows must have widget coverage
- all critical paths must have regression protection

---

# 2. Test Type Strategy

| Type | Purpose |
|------|--------|
| Unit | domain logic, use cases, pure functions |
| Widget | UI behavior, rendering, interaction |
| Integration | full user journeys |
| Golden | visual regression (only stable UI) |

---

## Rules

- [ ] prefer unit tests for logic
- [ ] prefer widget tests for UI behavior
- [ ] use integration tests sparingly (only critical flows)
- [ ] avoid overusing golden tests

---

# 3. File Structure Rules

## Required Structure

Tests MUST mirror `lib/` structure.

```
packages/features/conditions/test/data/go_no_go_profile_repository_test.dart
packages/features/map/test/launch_providers_test.dart
apps/eddyscout/test/screens/map_planning_provider_test.dart
```

---

## Rules

- [ ] test location must reflect source ownership
- [ ] test files must end in `_test.dart`
- [ ] maintain clear mapping between source and test

---

# 4. Mocking Rules

## Required Tooling

- MUST use `mocktail`
- MUST NOT use `mockito` unless explicitly required for legacy constraints

---

## Mocking Principles

- [ ] mock external dependencies only
- [ ] do not mock domain logic
- [ ] prefer fake implementations for complex systems
- [ ] keep mocks minimal and behavior-focused

---

# 5. Deterministic Test Rules

## MUST BE TRUE

Tests must NOT depend on:

- real network calls
- real databases
- real file system
- real time
- real randomness (without seeding)

---

## Required Tools

- `fakeAsync` → time-based logic
- `pump` / `pumpAndSettle` → widget async resolution
- in-memory fakes → storage/network simulation

---

## MUST NOT

- use real timers
- rely on animation timing without control
- depend on external services
- introduce flaky async behavior

---

# 6. Widget Testing Rules

## Required Coverage

Widget tests MUST cover:

- rendering states (loading / error / data / empty)
- user interactions (tap, input, scroll)
- provider integration (via overrides)
- responsive behavior where relevant

---

## Required Setup

- [ ] wrap widgets in `MaterialApp` (or app shell)
- [ ] wrap in `ProviderScope(overrides: ...)`
- [ ] ensure correct MediaQuery if needed

---

# 7. Integration Testing Rules

> **Current repo:** integration tests at `apps/eddyscout/integration_test/` (token gate + map → launch detail). See `docs/TESTING.md` and `make integration-test`.

## Required for:

- authentication flows
- onboarding flows
- payment flows (if applicable)
- multi-screen navigation journeys
- critical business workflows

---

## Rules

- [ ] run on real device/emulator
- [ ] avoid mocking core app layers
- [ ] isolate external services where possible
- [ ] treat as regression-critical tests

---

# 8. Test Naming Standards

## Preferred test description

Use behavior-oriented descriptions inside `test()`:

```
should [expected behavior] when [condition]
```

---

## Examples

- should return error when network request fails
- should display empty state when no items exist
- should redirect to missing-token route when Mapbox token is empty

---

## Rules

- [ ] test names must describe behavior, not implementation
- [ ] use `group()` to group related cases (by provider, widget, or class) — this is the common repo pattern
- [ ] avoid vague names like “test login”

---

# 9. Async Testing Rules

## Required Practices

- [ ] use `pump()` for frame advancement
- [ ] use `pumpAndSettle()` for full UI stabilization
- [ ] never rely on real-time delays
- [ ] control async execution explicitly

---

# 10. Coverage Requirements

## Enforcement

- [ ] coverage thresholds defined in `tooling/coverage.yaml`
- [ ] CI fails on coverage regression
- [ ] new code must include corresponding tests

---

## Command

```bash
flutter test --coverage
```

---

# 11. Anti-Patterns (DO NOT DO)

## MUST NOT

- test implementation details instead of behavior
- rely on real network or storage
- ignore async handling
- create flaky timing-dependent tests
- duplicate production logic in tests
- skip edge cases

---

## SHOULD AVOID

- excessive mocking of internal logic
- brittle UI selectors
- overly complex test setups
- integration tests for trivial logic

---

